                <a href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/02/product-of-the-month-arcteryx-alpha-ar-35-backpack/">
          <img class="teaser-image" src="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/amersports-wordpress-exove/uploads/20190219140510/alpha_ar_35_backpack_beacon_584x328.jpg" alt="Product of the month: Arc'teryx Alpha AR 35 backpack">
        </a>
                <div class="teaser-content">
          <h2 class="teaser-title"><a href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/02/product-of-the-month-arcteryx-alpha-ar-35-backpack/">Product of the month: Arc&#8217;teryx Alpha AR 35 backpack</a></h2>
          <time class="teaser-date" datetime="" itemprop="datePublished">February 19, 2019</time>
          <p>The new Alpha AR 35 is a durable and versatile single day pack for multi-pitch rock, alpine and ice climbing. Arc&#8217;teryx developed its own fabric to achieve the hardwearing durability necessary for climbing. Prioritizing abrasion and tear resistance, a liquid crystal polymer ripstop grid is incorporated in a high tenacity nylon fabric. Extremely versatile, customizable options suit the needs of alpine adventures. A removable framesheet and an adjustable, removable top lid give the option to shed weight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="teaser-buttons">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/02/product-of-the-month-arcteryx-alpha-ar-35-backpack/">
            Read more          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
            <div class="teaser">
                <a href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/02/atomic-racing-team-rocked-the-alpine-ski-world-championships/">
          <img class="teaser-image" src="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/amersports-wordpress-exove/uploads/20190218171759/Marcel-Hirscher-584x328.jpg" alt="Atomic racing team rocked the Alpine World Ski Championships">
        </a>
                <div class="teaser-content">
          <h2 class="teaser-title"><a href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/02/atomic-racing-team-rocked-the-alpine-ski-world-championships/">Atomic racing team rocked the Alpine World Ski Championships</a></h2>
          <time class="teaser-date" datetime="" itemprop="datePublished">February 18, 2019</time>
          <p>The Atomic racing team rocked the 45th FIS Skiing World Championships in Åre. With three gold, three silver, and three bronze medals, Atomic was the most successful skiing brand in the world, setting the benchmark in race intelligence, performance and commitment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="teaser-buttons">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/02/atomic-racing-team-rocked-the-alpine-ski-world-championships/">
            Read more          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
            <div class="teaser">
                <a href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/01/salomon-unveils-limited-edition-lo-fi-goggle-developed-with-nicolas-vuignier/">
          <img class="teaser-image" src="https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/amersports-wordpress-exove/uploads/20190130161056/MountainCo18_19_Domdaher_2-72-584x328.jpg" alt="Salomon unveils limited edition LO-FI goggle developed with Nicolas Vuignier">
        </a>
                <div class="teaser-content">
          <h2 class="teaser-title"><a href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/01/salomon-unveils-limited-edition-lo-fi-goggle-developed-with-nicolas-vuignier/">Salomon unveils limited edition LO-FI goggle developed with Nicolas Vuignier</a></h2>
          <time class="teaser-date" datetime="" itemprop="datePublished">January 30, 2019</time>
          <p>Salomon has a long history of putting performance first and relying on the leaders of the sport to drive the direction of products. The new Limited Edition LO-FI goggle was developed in close collaboration with Salomon freeski team member and all-around creative talent Nicolas Vuignier.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="teaser-buttons">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="https://www.amersports.com/2019/01/salomon-unveils-limited-edition-lo-fi-goggle-developed-with-nicolas-vuignier/">
            Read more          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
        </div>
  
            </article><!-- #post-## -->
